Path: README.md
 1	# GORM Repository
 2	
 3	A generic repository pattern implementation for GORM with advanced features including transaction management, entity diffing, and pagination.
 4	
 5	## Features
 6	
 7	- **Generic Repository Pattern**: Type-safe repository operations using Go generics
 8	- **Transaction Management**: Built-in transaction support with automatic rollback/commit
 9	- **Entity Diffing**: Track and update only changed fields using the `Diffable` interface
 10	- **Pagination**: Built-in pagination with comprehensive metadata
 11	- **Association Management**: Append, remove, and replace entity associations
 12	- **Flexible Querying**: Functional options for customizing queries
 13	- **Utilities**: CamelCase naming strategy and entity-to-map conversion
 14	
 15	## Installation
 16	
 17	```bash
 18	go get github.com/ikateclab/gorm-repository
 19	```
 20	
 21	## Quick Start
 22	
 23	### Basic Usage
 24	
 25	```go
 26	import (
 27	 "github.com/ikateclab/gorm-repository/repositories"
 28	 "gorm.io/gorm"
 29	)
 30	
 31	// Create a repository for your entity
 32	type User struct {
 33	 ID uuid.UUID `gorm:"type:text;primary_key"`
 34	 Name string
 35	 Email string
 36	 Age int
 37	}
 38	
 39	// Initialize repository
 40	db := // your GORM database instance
 41	userRepo := repositories.NewGormRepository[User](db)
 42	
 43	// Basic operations
 44	ctx := context.Background()
 45	
 46	// Create
 47	user := User{ID: uuid.New(), Name: "John", Email: "john@example.com"}
 48	err := userRepo.Create(ctx, user)
 49	
 50	// Find by ID
 51	user, err := userRepo.FindById(ctx, userID)
 52	
 53	// Find many with options
 54	users, err := userRepo.FindMany(ctx, 
 55	 repositories.WithQuery(func(db *gorm.DB) *gorm.DB {
 56	 return db.Where("age > ?", 18)
 57	 }),
 58	)
...
 203	```
